status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Solving the problem
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
From 14.451, with concave utility and exponential discounting, we can:
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pause
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Use a variational approach, find the asset path that satisfies Euler equation
 and transversality
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pause
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Set up the problem recursively, and walk down Bellman's road
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pause
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
They give the same solution in this context, as the conditions for the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

sufficiency theorem
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 hold (see Alp's 14.661 notes and Daron's book 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Introduction to Modern Economic Growth
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

):
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pause
\end_layout

\end_inset


