\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
By the above conditions, let's solve the problem 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
V_{t}(A_{t}|\mathcal{I}_{t})= & \max_{h_{t},c_{t}}U(c_{t},h_{t})+\frac{1}{1+\rho}E_{t}V_{t+1}(A_{t+1}|\mathcal{I}_{t+1})\\
\text{s.t.} & \ A_{t+1}=(1+r_{t})A_{t}+w_{t}h_{t}-c_{t}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pause
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $V_{t}(A_{t}|\mathcal{I}_{t})$
\end_inset

 is the optimum value function given available information in 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{I}_{t}$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pause
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
State variable is accumulated assets at time 
\begin_inset Formula $t,\ A_{t},$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The constraint is the law of motion of the agent's assets
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
FOCs
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
Replacing 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{t+1}=(1+r_{t})A_{t}+w_{t}h_{t}-c_{t}$
\end_inset

 in the Bellman equation, we can get the following f.o.c.'s 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pause
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
c_{t}:\quad U_{c}(c_{t},h_{t})-\frac{1}{1+\rho}E_{t}[V_{t+1}'(A_{t+1})] & = & 0\\
h_{t}:\quad U_{h}(c_{t},h_{t})+\frac{1}{1+\rho}w_{t}E_{t}[V_{t+1}'(A_{t+1})] & = & 0
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pause
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
To solve the problem, we also add the 
\emph on
envelope condition
\emph default
: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
A_{t}:\quad V_{t}'(A_{t})=\frac{1}{1+\rho}(1+r_{t})E_{t}[V_{t+1}'(A_{t+1})]\label{ET}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pause
\end_layout

\end_inset

This relates the MU of wealth today to the expected MU of wealth tomorrow
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame

\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout FrameTitle
MU of wealth
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Frame
Define the MU of wealth at time 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\lambda_{t}\equiv V_{t}'(A_{t}|\mathcal{I}_{t})
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

Then 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "ET"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 gives: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\lambda_{t}=\frac{1+r_{t}}{1+\rho}E_{t}[\lambda_{t+1}]
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame

\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout FrameTitle
Euler equations
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Frame
Plugging in we get two Euler equations: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
U_{c}(c_{t},h_{t}) & =\frac{1}{1+r_{t}}\lambda_{t}=E_{t}\left[\frac{1+r_{t+1}}{1+\rho}U_{c}(c_{t+1},h_{t+1})\right]\label{MUC}\\
U_{h}(c_{t},h_{t}) & =-\frac{w_{t}}{1+r_{t}}\lambda_{t}=E_{t}\left[\frac{1+r_{t+1}}{1+\rho}\frac{w_{t}}{w_{t+1}}U_{h}(c_{t+1},h_{t+1})\right]\label{MUL}
\end{align}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pause
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
As in class with one difference.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{t}$
\end_inset

 is no longer time invariant : 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lambda_{t}=\frac{1+r_{t}}{1+\rho}E_{t}\left[\lambda_{t+1}\right]=E_{t}\left[\Pi_{s=t}^{T-1}\frac{1+r_{s}}{1+\rho}\lambda_{T}\right]
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pause
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
summarizes the expected path of the MU of wealth in all future periods given
 current information
\end_layout

\end_deeper
